<h1>Assign row or column number to grid cells</h1>

<p>
This tool can be used to create a new raster with the same co-ordinates and demensions (i.e. rows and columns) as an existing base image. Grid cells in the new raster will be assigned either the row or column number or the x- or y-coordinate, depending on the selected option. The user must also specify the name of the base image and the data type (either <i>float</i> or <i>integer</i>). x- or y-coordinate images must be float since most co-ordinate systems require larger numbers than are able to fit within the allowable range of an integer value.</p>
<p>Notice that the functionality of this tool is replicated by the <a href="RasterCalculator.html"><b><i>Raster Calculator</b></i></a> operations <b><i>ColumnNumber</b></i>, <b><i>RowNumber</b></i>, <b><i>XCoordinate</b></i>, and <b><i>YCoordinate</b></i>.</p>


